content.text:
Done. Updated `ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_HAIKU_MODEL` from `claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929` to `claude-sonnet-4-6-20250514`.

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
`ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_HAIKU_MODEL` is an env var that overrides which model Claude Code actually uses when it would normally pick Haiku (e.g., for subagent calls with `model: "haiku"`). By pointing it at Sonnet 4.6, those "haiku-tier" calls get the full Sonnet 4.6 capability instead — useful when you want better quality from lightweight agent dispatches without changing every call site. The tradeoff is cost and latency, since Sonnet is heavier than Haiku.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
